    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. some of my more conservative students might argue that substantive due process is just \"judicial activism\" and that judges shouldn't be making up rights that aren't explicitly written in the Constitution. how should I address that critique in the lesson?",
      "source": "evaluator"
